In short, the Cohesive supergroup anthology better matches my core desires for layered, album‑oriented rock with punch, multi‑vocal interplay and singalong hooks, while Up!’s acoustic, twangy, confessional country approach conflicts with my dislike of intimate, folk‑adjacent textures and lacks the riff‑forward, stadium‑ready rock attack I prize.

